column1: These are the DSM elements we have time series for from CalLite-CV (that's the full name, there's a completely separate model called CalLite naturally). I used the names from your Google Doc (https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1FpO5moi003WxAz0-RqLlGkueru8lzsOtWV94rKkpzsc). The dates are the CalLite-CV dates: October 2014 in CalLite-CV corresponds to October 1925 in CalSim II in terms of model calibration, for reference. These results are the Outflow elements of each site listed on the Google Doc as of 1 PM 100417 (I saved those matches in another csv called 'matches for master csv.csv'. I left the Delta out of this for now... POTENTIAL PROBLEM: I'm noticing many 0-outflow months for NewHogan which is our Calaveras number. It's possible we could use the Calaveras_River node to get around this, even though it's below the anadromy limit; I think it's only got a 0 in the first month of the model run.
